            <q>Mr. Prescott is known to privately favour the scrapping of the Barnett Formula"&#x2014;</q>
            I intervened on the right hon. Member for Gateshead, East and Washington, West, and she said the same&#x2014;
            <q>which awards Scotland &#x00A3;537 per head more than the north-east, &#x00A3;938 per head more than the north-west, and &#x00A3;1,166 more than Yorkshire.</q>
            If the right hon. Lady is in favour of scrapping the Barnett formula, that automatically means that she is in favour of giving less money to the Scottish people and more to those in the north-east. However, the soon-to-become-Labour Mayor of London is in favour of more money being kept in London and less going to the north. If northern Members think that they are going to get more resources, they are in for a great surprise.
